<h1>LG Washer Control Board Replacement Cost</h1>

<p>Replacing the main control board on an LG washer costs $300–420 in Los Angeles — it's the brain of the machine, so when it fails you get dead panels, random codes, or a washer that ignores its own buttons. It's also the part most often blamed wrongly, so we test it properly before quoting a board you may not need. The $65 diagnostic is waived with the repair. Call (323) 990-7550.</p>

<h2>Cost Breakdown</h2>
<p>A control board job is the opposite of a teardown-heavy repair: the part is the expensive piece and the labor is modest. An OEM main board is the bulk of the $300–420, with roughly an hour to an hour and a half to swap it in, transfer settings, and test the machine through a cycle. That's why we're careful about confirming the board before ordering one — it's the costliest single part to get wrong.</p>

<h2>Make Sure It's Actually the Board</h2>
<p>Plenty of "control board" symptoms turn out to be something cheaper. A dead panel can be a failed line filter or power issue rather than the board, which our guide to an <a href="/washer/symptoms/lg-washer-wont-turn-on/">LG washer that won't turn on</a> walks through. A washer that lights up but ignores Start is often a door lock or a setting, covered in our guide to an <a href="/washer/symptoms/lg-washer-not-starting/">LG washer that won't start</a>. Random codes can trace to a hall sensor or loose wiring. Our techs test those first, because replacing a board that wasn't the problem is an expensive mistake we'd rather you never pay for.</p>

<h2>Repair vs Replace</h2>
<p>On a newer LG washer, a $300–420 board against $800–1,500 for a comparable new machine is a clear win — the rest of the washer has years left. On an older machine that's already losing other parts, a fresh board may not be the smartest spend, and we'll give you an honest read on-site rather than push a repair that won't pay off.</p>

<h2>What's Included</h2>
<p>The price covers the OEM control board, the labor to install, configure, and test it, and a one-year warranty on parts and labor. The $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair, and we confirm the board is genuinely the fault before quoting so you're never paying for a part the machine didn't need.</p>

