<h2>Frequently Asked Questions — LG Washer Control Board Replacement Cost</h2>

<h3>How much does LG washer control board replacement cost?</h3>
<p>LG washer control board replacement costs $300–420 installed in Los Angeles with an OEM board. The board itself is the bulk of the price; labor is about an hour. The $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair.</p>

<h3>How do I know it's the control board and not something cheaper?</h3>
<p>You usually don't from the symptoms alone — a dead panel, random codes, or unresponsive buttons can all come from a door lock, a hall sensor, or loose wiring, not the board. We test those first, because the control board is the most expensive part to wrongly replace. We're licensed with the Bureau of Household Goods and Services (#49573).</p>

<h3>Why is the control board one of the costlier LG washer repairs?</h3>
<p>Because the part itself is expensive — the main board is the machine's computer, and an OEM replacement isn't cheap. Labor is modest by comparison, so most of the $300–420 is the board, which is exactly why we confirm it's the real fault first.</p>

<h3>Is replacing the control board worth it or should I replace the washer?</h3>
<p>On a newer LG washer, yes — $300–420 versus $800–1,500 for a new machine. On an older washer with other parts already failing, a new control board may not be the smartest spend, and we'll give you an honest read before you commit.</p>

<h3>Can a power surge damage my LG washer control board?</h3>
<p>Yes — surges and brownouts are a common cause of control-board failure, which is why a board can die suddenly on an otherwise healthy washer. If yours failed after an outage or surge, a plug-in surge protector is cheap insurance for the new board.</p>

